cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SI 

This paper discusses a machine learning technique (Support Vector Data Description) and proposes an empirical criteria for selecting a parameter value. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The technique is applied to outlier detection, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the effect of kernel function parameters, which is relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) and statistical learning (cs.SI).
